text: Xanthostemon psidioides is a shrub or tree species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Australia. The spreading shrub or tree typically grows to a height of . It blooms in May producing cream-white coloured flowers. It is found on and the base of sandstone cliffs in the Kimberley region of Western Australia near the Walcott Inlet and the Prince Regent National Park. ==References== psidioides Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Plants described in 1982 Category:Flora of the Northern Territory
